headline.main: The Week's Morality and the Causes.

docs.lead_paragraph: Four hundred and forty burials last week--just one more than the week before, and at least one hundred and one more than it ought to be, or probably would be, if the laws of health were at all understood. or where understood, generally acted upon. True, this is in reality a reduction from the mortality of the preceding week.

headline.main: MORAL AND RELIGIOUS.; Church and Missionary Intelligence.

docs.lead_paragraph: According to the United States Census, the Methodists are the most numerous and most wealthy of all the sects. The Baptists, in point of numbers are the next, and the Presbyterians next in wealth, and very near the same as the Methodists.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; MILITARY. THE VISIT OF THE BOSTON CITY GUARDS. Grand Dinner at the Irving House. THE INGRAHAM DEMONSTRATION A TERRIBLE AFFRAY. FIRE IN VESEY-STREET. THE ROBBERY AT UNION COURSE. JURISDICTION OF THE ARCHBISHOP. THE PRIZE-FIGHT. BANQUET BY THE BININGER GUARD. ANOTHER RAILROAD ACCIDENT. SIGNOR BLITZ AT STUYVESANT INSTITUTE. THE POLICY GAMBLING CASE. DESERTER FROM THE NAVY. BURGLARY AND ARREST. RUN OVER. WASHINGTON MONUMENT. U. S. DISTRICT COURT.

docs.lead_paragraph: The New York City Guards have shown themselves worthy of noble guests. The "Crack Companies " of the two great cities enjoyed themselves last night. The New-York City Guard, in their arrangements for their guests' entertainment, appointed last evening for a grand dinner at the Irving House, which duly came off in a magnificent style, worthy of the citizen- soldiers who were feasted and those who gave the feast. It was truly a great time.
